properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 9 at 1:04AM MST until February 9 at 8:00AM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
The combination of accumulating snow and gusty northwest winds
has brought considerable travel impacts across northern Johnson
County this morning. Significant blowing and drifting snow will
continue along I-25 and I-90 through the middle of Sunday
morning.

* WHAT...Snow. Additional snow accumulations of up to two inch.
Winds gusting as high as 45 mph.

* WHERE...Northeast Johnson County.

* WHEN...Until 8 AM MST this morning.

* IMPACTS...Travel will be very difficult on I-25 and I-90.
Blowing snow could significantly reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 AM MST THIS MORNING
